def transform_dataset(input_list):
    output_list = []
    header = input_list[0]
    
    for row in input_list[1:]:
        name = row[0]
        for i in range(1, len(row)):
            if row[i]:
                output_list.append([name, header[i], row[i]])
    
    print(output_list)

# Example of calling the function with the input list
transform_dataset([['', 'Qual 1', 'Qual 2', 'Qual 3'], ['Ben', '31.08.2001', '', '05.07.2004'], ['Carl', '', '18.04.2003', '09.12.2009']])
